ese results is our general framework for saddle-point problems, which may be\nof independent interest. This framework, in turn is based on our proposed\nAccelerated Meta-Algorithm for composite optimization with probabilistic\ninexact oracles and probabilistic inexactness in the proximal mapping, which\nmay be of independent interest as well.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 16 Mar 2021 22:08:09 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 14 Jun 2021 13:21:13 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-06-15"}
